########################################################
salomeToROOT 

Is a tool developed at UNAM Engineering 
Institute as part of the research group GITA, aims 
to be a bridge enters tools and platform salome ROOT 
framework is the first version of this tool, therefore 
limited to only 6 basic geometric primitives.
Currently the group is developing a person and began 
in July 2012.
Distributed under the GNU GPL


########################################################
########################################################
System Requirements
 
• GNU/LINUX 
• Compiler gcc
• Compiler bison
• Compiler flex

########################################################
########################################################
Installation

There is a makefile, so installation is simple the 
steps are:

• SalomeToROOT.tar.gz Unzip the file in / opt

	> cd /opt

•We enter the folder salomeToROOT: 

	> cd salomeToROOT

•Run the command make:

	> make

•Execute with superuser permission command 
make install:

	# make install

Further options include uninstall and
clean, to uninstall and clean respectively. 

########################################################
########################################################
Use

salomeToROOT is a command line tool, to be used from the 
command line call the translator with the following syntax:

	salomeToROOT name_file.py


